# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Docker build context excludes — repo-root context (monorepo).
# Applied to both apps/fanaa/Dockerfile and services/api/Dockerfile builds.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Per-workspace install trees — pnpm regenerates these inside the image.
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Build outputs — Next.js regenerates these inside the image.
.next
**/.next
out
.vercel
.turbo
**/.turbo

# Local env files — only .env.example variants are allowed in.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!**/.env.example
!**/.env.admin.example

# VCS + IDE noise.
.git
.gitignore
.idea
.vscode
.cursor

# ── BUT keep the git metadata required for build-time SHA derivation ────────
# `apps/studio/Dockerfile` (post-M12-deployment-pipeline-fix) reads
# `.git/HEAD` + `.git/refs/heads/<branch>` (loose) or `.git/packed-refs`
# (packed) to stamp the build SHA without relying on a hand-typed
# `STUDIO_BUILD_SHA` build arg in EasyPanel. The object database
# (objects/, pack/, hooks/, config, index) stays excluded — we ship
# only ≈8 KB of refs metadata, not the entire git history.
#
# DO NOT remove these exceptions without also reverting the auto-SHA
# block in apps/studio/Dockerfile. The build would silently regress
# to the literal string "dev" on every deploy.
!.git/HEAD
!.git/refs
!.git/refs/**
!.git/packed-refs

# Logs + caches.
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.DS_Store
.cache
coverage
playwright-report
test-results

# Documentation — keep PLATFORM.md out of the image but allow README.md.
*.md
!README.md

# Cross-workspace exclusions —
# The fanaa Docker build doesn't need services/ (the FastAPI tree),
# and the services/api build doesn't see apps/ because its build context
# is scoped to ./services/api by docker-compose.
services
